 spelled  <b>Christianna</b> , under the influence of the name   Anna ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705207,"age":8,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":10,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705210,"age":23,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705212,"age":43,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Mary Christiana Filby was born on 10 March 1576, in Wilby, Suffolk, England, her father, John Filby, was 24 and her mother, Lydia Bootman, was 26. She married John Gorball on 20 April 1590, in Wilby, Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died in 1620, in her hometown, at the age of 44."},"et":{"10 Mar 1576–1620":"10. märts 1576–1620","1576–1620":"1576–1620","1575–1615":"1575–1615","1575–Male":"1575–Surnud","1592–1622":"1592–1622","1598–1667":"1598–1667","1623–Female":"1623–Surnud","1551–1582":"1551–1582","1550–1600":"1550–1600","1550":"1550","1582":"1582","1592":"1592","1623":"1623","1667":"1667","1600":"1600","1622":"1622","10 Mar 1576":"10. märts 1576","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1598":"1598","1576":"1576","1575":"1575","1585":"1585","Abt. 1598":"umbes 1598","1551":"1551","Aft 1582":"pärast 1582","20 April 1590":"20. aprill 1590","about 1575":"umbes 1575","1615":"1615","Wilby, Suffolk, England":"Wilby, Suffolk, England","Dennington, Suffolk, England":"Dennington, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wrentham, Suffolk, England":"Wrentham, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"10 Mar 1576–1620":"10. maaliskuuta 1576–1620","1576–1620":"1576–1620","1575–1615":"1575–1615","1575–Male":"1575–Kuollut","1592–1622":"1592–1622","1598–1667":"1598–1667","1623–Female":"1623–Kuollut","1551–1582":"1551–1582","1550–1600":"1550–1600","1550":"1550","1582":"1582","1592":"1592","1623":"1623","1667":"1667","1600":"1600","1622":"1622","10 Mar 1576":"10. maaliskuuta 1576","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1598":"1598","1576":"1576","1575":"1575","1585":"1585","Abt. 1598":"noin 1598","1551":"1551","Aft 1582":"1582 jälkeen","20 April 1590":"20. huhtikuuta 1590","about 1575":"noin 1575","1615":"1615","Wilby, Suffolk, England":"Wilby, Suffolk, England","Dennington, Suffolk, England":"De